        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:2:3:72:1",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/3/72/1",
        "text": [
          " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : «إِنَّمَا يُكْرَهُ أَنْ يَجْمَعَ اَلرَّجُلُ بَيْنَ اَلسُّبُوعَيْنِ وَ اَلطَّوَافَيْنِ فِي اَلْفَرِيضَةِ فَأَمَّا فِي اَلنَّافِلَةِ فَلاَ بَأْسَ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.2816 - Ibn Muskan narrated from Zurara, who said that Abu Abdullah (as) said:\n\"It is only disliked for a person to combine two sets of seven circuits (tawafayn) in the obligatory tawaf. However, in the case of voluntary tawaf, there is no issue.\""
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1250,
        "local_index": 2,
        "narrator_chain": {
          "parts": [
            {
